text:
\begin{equation}
E_{\rm flare} \sim f E_{\rm mag} \sim \frac{fB^2 L^3}{8\pi} \sim \frac{f B^2 A_{\rm spot}^{3/2}}{8\pi} ,
\label{e_flare}
\end{equation}

\begin{equation}
\tau _{\rm flare} \sim \tau _{\rm rec} \sim \tau _{\rm A}/M_{\rm A} \sim L/v_{\rm A}/M_{\rm A},
\label{flare_duration}
\end{equation}

nexttext:
This suggests that the power-law slope for the 
correlation between the flare duration 
and flare energy is about $1/3$ which is comparable to the 
observed value of $0.39\pm 0.03$.


